On Schnitzler's 50th birthday, Sigmund Freud wrote him a letter expressing his profound admiration and acknowledging the writer as his alter ego. Schnitzler, however, kept his distance. He thought life was more complicated than psychoanalysis allowed. In his only novel, he skewered Vienna's Jews and exposed the coldness at the heart of Vienna's easy sentimentality.</pbcoreDescription><pbcoreCreator><creator>WGBH Forum Network</creator><creatorRole>Production Unit</creatorRole></pbcoreCreator><pbcoreCreator><creator ref="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n50052713">WGBH Educational Foundation</creator><creatorRole>Producing Organization</creatorRole></pbcoreCreator><pbcoreInstantiation><instantiationIdentifier source="WGBH Item ID">25623</instantiationIdentifier><instantiationIdentifier source="WGBH Barcode">0000330457</instantiationIdentifier><instantiationIdentifier source="WGBH File Number">CD Case</instantiationIdentifier><instantiationDate dateType="created">2010-09-01</instantiationDate><instantiationPhysical>DVD</instantiationPhysical><instantiationLocation>HOLDINGS_LOCATION = Vault.  Vault-ML004962----</instantiationLocation><instantiationMediaType>Moving Image</instantiationMediaType><instantiationGenerations>Original</instantiationGenerations><instantiationTracks>Audio:  tracks</instantiationTracks><instantiationEssenceTrack><essenceTrackType>General</essenceTrackType><essenceTrackStandard>NTSC</essenceTrackStandard><essenceTrackFrameRate>29.97</essenceTrackFrameRate><essenceTrackAspectRatio>4:3</essenceTrackAspectRatio></instantiationEssenceTrack><instantiationAnnotation annotationType="organization">WGBH</instantiationAnnotation></pbcoreInstantiation><pbcoreAnnotation annotationType="last_modified">2013-06-22 16:33:33</pbcoreAnnotation><pbcoreAnnotation annotationType="organization">WGBH</pbcoreAnnotation></pbcoreDescriptionDocument>
